const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const cors = require('cors');

app.disable('x-powered-by');
app.use(helmet());
app.use(cors({ origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGIN, methods: ['GET'] }));
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 100 }));
```

- `helmet` sets sensible default headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Content-Type-Options, etc.).
- `rate-limit` mitigates brute-force / DoS.
- Explicit CORS origin avoids the permissive default.
- `x-powered-by` leaks the framework name.

## 4. Sensitive data exposure on `/users`

`/users` returns emails unauthenticated. Even with mock data, this sets a bad precedent. Protect the route behind authentication and only return fields the caller is allowed to see:

