app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not Found' }));

process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => console.error('UnhandledRejection', reason));
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => { console.error('UncaughtException', err); process.exit(1); });
```
Never return `err.message` or `err.stack` to the client in production — that leaks implementation details.

## 2. No input validation

**Issue:** Routes don't currently take input, but `/users` will almost certainly grow query params (`?id=`, `?limit=`) or a `POST /users` body. Without validation, those become SQLi / NoSQLi / prototype-pollution vectors.

