app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

Never log request bodies or headers verbatim — they can contain tokens.

## 8. Graceful shutdown

On SIGTERM/SIGINT, stop accepting new connections so in-flight requests finish cleanly:

```js
const server = app.listen(PORT, ...);
for (const sig of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {
  process.on(sig, () => server.close(() => process.exit(0)));
}
```

