- Add input-validation unit tests per endpoint (valid, invalid, boundary, malicious — e.g., `../../etc/passwd`, very large numbers, unicode).
- Consider TypeScript or `// @ts-check` with JSDoc for compile-time safety on request/response shapes.

---

### Suggested priority order
1. Helmet + `x-powered-by` off + global error middleware (quick wins)
2. Schema validation on every new endpoint (prevents most input bugs)
3. Rate limiting + body size limits
4. AuthN/AuthZ on `/users` before exposing PII
5. Graceful shutdown and env-driven config

