- Don't return raw error messages or stack traces to clients (see §2).

## 6. Hard-coded port & logging

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

Use a structured logger (`pino`, `winston`) instead of `console.log`, and never log secrets, tokens, or PII.

## 7. Async route safety

When you add async handlers, wrap them so rejected promises reach the error middleware:

```js
const asyncHandler = (fn) => (req, res, next) => Promise.resolve(fn(req, res, next)).catch(next);
app.get('/users', asyncHandler(async (req, res) => { /* ... */ }));
```

(Express 5 handles this natively; Express 4 does not.)

## 8. Graceful shutdown

Capture the server instance and close it on `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` so in-flight requests aren't dropped and DB connections are released cleanly.

